Package: convexr
Type: Package
Title: An R package for Disciplined Convex Programming through Convex.jl
Version: 0.2.0
Authors@R: person("Changcheng Li", email = "cxl508@psu.edu",
    role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: convexr provides a simple wrapper for Convex.jl,
    which makes it easy to describe and solve convex optimization problems in R.
    The problems can be dealt with include:
    linear programs,
    second-order cone programs (SOCP),
    semidefinite programs (SDP),
    exponential cone programs.
License: Apache License | file LICENSE
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: true
Imports: XRJulia,
    magrittr
RoxygenNote: 6.0.1
Suggests: testthat,
    knitr,
    rmarkdown,
    plotrix
VignetteBuilder: knitr
SystemRequirements: Julia >= 0.5.0,
    Convex.jl (will install automatically into Julia if not founded)
    SCS.jl (will install automatically into Julia if not found)
